        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/lion1969/{size}/6977_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-08-30T09:43:55.555Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Since v7.14 Signal on Android has a new and nice looking unlock screen with it’s animation.</p>\n<p>On a Pixel phone with on-screen fingerprint reader, this new animation starts after the regular android/pixel unlock animation completes making the complete unlock process annoyingly longer than it used to be.</p>\n<p>A few days ago I saw <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/disabling-the-new-unlock-animation/62432\">this request</a> for an option to disable the new animation, but maybe a better approach could be detecting how long the Android animation takes to complete and speed up Signal’s own unlock animation accordingly to reach a less intrusive total length of the unlock process.</p>\n<p>Is anyone else here feeling this delay in opening the app annoying?<br>\nAny ideas?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2024-08-30T09:43:55.555Z",
